text:
Diet number 9 for diabetes
Diet for diabetes: indications for use, basic principles, an approximate menu
06 Nov 2019, 10:00 by Daria Kabackis
Diet No. 9 was developed for patients with type 2 diabetes of moderate and mild severity. This diet is suitable not only for diabetics, but also for those who want to lose weight on a healthy diet without strict restrictions. The diet ration is balanced in such a way that the body receives all the necessary substances, vitamins and trace elements, so such nutrition is beneficial and helps maintain an optimal level in the blood.
Diet No. 9 for type 2 diabetes: basic principles
Despite the fact that diet No. 9 is recognized as a special therapeutic diet, it allows you to lose weight. The main goal of this diet is to create conditions within the body that normalize carbohydrate metabolism.
The basic principles of the diet:

Exclusion of fast (harmful) carbohydrates.
Culinary processing of dishes: cooking, stewing, baking, frying without breadcrumbs and butter.
Eating at least 5-6 times a day.
The approximate chemical composition of diet No. 9: 100 g of protein, 70−80 g of fat (mainly plant origin), 300 g of complex carbohydrates.
The approximate daily caloric content of diet No. 9 is 1500–2300 kcal.
There are several varieties of diet No. 9, but the average option suits most thanks to a specially designed system.

Table number 9 with high sugar: products
The average version of diet No. 9 allows and prohibits certain foods.
Approved and recommended products include:

coarse bran bread and bakery products, diabetic varieties;
vegetarian soups on vegetable broth;
soups from lean meats and fish;
low-fat varieties of meat and fish, steamed and other permitted methods;
vegetables: different kinds of cabbage, lettuce, eggplant, zucchini, pumpkin, legumes, tomatoes, cucumbers, carrots and other root vegetables, bell pepper, celery, tarragon, herbs and other vegetables in raw or processed form;
unsweetened varieties of fruits and berries: green apples, pears, quinces, plums, citrus fruits, peaches, cherries, currants, gooseberries, lingonberries, raspberries, strawberries, cranberries, mountain ash in raw, dried form, in sugarless compotes;
dishes from cereals and pasta of hard varieties, cereals and casseroles from millet, buckwheat, oatmeal;
egg dishes: soft-boiled, hard-boiled, fried eggs, omelet, casserole, as well as in other dishes;
dairy products: low fat or low fat, without added sugar and preservatives; kefir, yogurt, milk, cheese, cream, butter;
confectionery products with sugar substitute only, which can be purchased in the diabetic department: unsweetened waffles, marmalade, marshmallows, healthy bars;
vegetable oil: sunflower, corn, coconut and others;
drinks: tea, coffee without sugar and syrups, drinking water, natural vegetable and fruit juices without sweeteners.

Prohibited Products:




sugar, confectionery and pastries, chocolate and other sweets;
goose meat, ducks, smoked fish and sausages, sausages;
baked milk, sweet dairy products with additives;
meat and artificial fats;
rice, semolina, low quality pasta;
grapes, bananas, raisins, dried fruits with the addition of syrups and sugar;
spicy, smoked, spicy and other dishes with additives;
fried foods;
sweet fruits;
pickled vegetables, pickles;
sweet soda, alcoholic drinks.

Diet No. 9 for type 2 diabetes: a sample menu
Diet number 9 allows you to make the most balanced menu, based on the principles of healthy eating. A limited intake of carbohydrates leads not only to the stabilization of blood sugar, but also helps to get rid of extra pounds, puffiness. Table diet No. 9 has a positive effect on the skin condition: adhering to the principles of such nutrition, you can get rid of rashes, acne and other troubles.
A set of foods for the day should include a variety of foods, so try to maintain a balance of proteins, fats and complex carbohydrates, so as not to harm your health.
The menu for the day can be composed approximately in this way:

butter - 20 g;
nonfat milk - 200 ml;
kefir - 200 ml;
cottage cheese - 100 g;
sour cream - 40 g;
cereals - 50 g;
tomatoes - 20 g;
cabbage - 600 g;
carrots - 75 g;
greens - 30 g;
fish - 100 g;
beef or chicken - 150 g;
fruit - 100 g;
bran or diabetic bread - 200 g.

Sample diet menu number 9

Breakfast: oatmeal on the water, half an avocado, a cup of coffee without sugar.
Snack: a handful of almonds.
Lunch: 100 g of boiled fish, 200 g of fresh vegetables with a drop of vegetable oil, orange.
Snack: 200 g fat-free cottage cheese, a cup of green tea.
Dinner: 150 g of baked chicken, boiled broccoli, 200 g of fresh vegetable salad with a drop of vegetable oil.
Late dinner: a glass of kefir, soft-boiled egg.

